- At a false acceptance rate of 0.01%, the corresponding threshold is 90.
- At a false acceptance rate of 0.1%, the corresponding threshold is 80.
- At a false acceptance rate of 1%, the corresponding threshold is 60.

> This field only represents the comparison result between the face and the authoritative data and serves as a reference score. We do not recommend using this score alone as the pass/fail criterion. For the comprehensive verification result, refer to the **VerifyStatus** field. The **VerifyStatus** result combines the face-to-authoritative-data comparison with multiple other strategies to improve the security level.', example='97'),
